<div id="review_2390505218" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2390505218" />
    <a title="Sunshine Rodgers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57130264-sunshine-rodgers"><img alt="Sunshine Rodgers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643743839p2/57130264.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2390505218?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sunshine Rodgers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sunshine Rodgers" href="/user/show/57130264-sunshine-rodgers">Sunshine Rodgers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2390505218" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11417692829141567695">So I always love reading anything by C.S. Lewis. He is my go-to author! This book is basically Lewis just talking about his insights and his perspectives on love. It&apos;s almost like I am out with him drinking coffee at the cafe and he&apos;s just sharing his thoughts on love and friendship. There was a lot of contradictions i.e. sex without love can be a good thing...friendship can be a bad thing. And I was like, &quot;Okay...explain.&quot; And Lewis *does* explain and offers terrific ideals and values on love, </span>
  <span id="freeText11417692829141567695" style="display:none">So I always love reading anything by C.S. Lewis. He is my go-to author! This book is basically Lewis just talking about his insights and his perspectives on love. It's almost like I am out with him drinking coffee at the cafe and he's just sharing his thoughts on love and friendship. There was a lot of contradictions i.e. sex without love can be a good thing...friendship can be a bad thing. And I was like, "Okay...explain." And Lewis *does* explain and offers terrific ideals and values on love, friendship, Affection, Charity and the like. For anyone who loves hearing Lewis "talk", this is a great book to read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11417692829141567695" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


