<div id="review_2506607308" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2506607308" />
    <a title="John" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2763719-john"><img alt="John" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1638938390p2/2763719.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2506607308?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John" href="/user/show/2763719-john">John</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2763719-john?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2763719-john?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2763719-john?shelf=christian-studies">christian-studies</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2506607308" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8777567597047869072">Where most books on love give food for thought, THE FOUR LOVES offers a king&apos;s banquet. There is more wisdom in one page of this book than in the entirety of Erich Fromm&apos;s THE ART OF LOVING.<br/>Love is a messy subject, so it&apos;s only natural that Lewis&apos; analysis be a bit messy as well. And though he&apos;s incredibly methodical in shaping his ideas and presenting them with art and diplomacy, Lewis writes with such warmth and accessibility that we view him as the sagely uncle we all dearly wish we had.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText8777567597047869072" style="display:none">Where most books on love give food for thought, THE FOUR LOVES offers a king's banquet. There is more wisdom in one page of this book than in the entirety of Erich Fromm's THE ART OF LOVING.<br />Love is a messy subject, so it's only natural that Lewis' analysis be a bit messy as well. And though he's incredibly methodical in shaping his ideas and presenting them with art and diplomacy, Lewis writes with such warmth and accessibility that we view him as the sagely uncle we all dearly wish we had.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8777567597047869072" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


